==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fetterbush
<hw>fet"ter*bush`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An ornamental
evergreen shrub (<spn>Pieris floribunda</spn>) of the Southeastern U. S.
having small white bell-shaped flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mountain fetterbush, mountain andromeda, <spn>Pieris
floribunda</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A showy evergreen shrub (<spn>Lyonia lucida</spn>)
of the Southeastern U. S. with shiny leaves and angled branches and
umbel-like clusters of pink to reddish flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fetter bush, shiny lyonia, <spn>Lyonia
lucida</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fettered</ent>⟦br⟧
